GUIpack

Class MapNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • GUIpack.MapNode

  • public class MapNode
extends java.lang.Object
    A MapNode based on a node in graph theory. A MapNode can be a point along the path or a building depending on how nodeInfo is assigned.
    Author:
    Douglas Wallin

      • x

      • y

        The y coordinate (pixel)

      • nodeId

        private final java.lang.String nodeId
        This stores information which will be used to lookup nodes with null nodeInfo. It will be of the format "xcoordinate,ycoordinate"

      • nodeInfo

        private java.lang.String nodeInfo
        A string to describe what a MapNode is. Will be typically used to distinguish a building from a point along the path

      • MapNode

        public MapNode(int x,
               int y,
               java.lang.String nodeInfo)
        Alternate constructor used primarily for MapNodes that designate a building or important point. Requires nodeInfo (usually the building name or a short description, i.e. "Police HQ").
        Parameters:
        x - int: The x coordinate of the node
        y - int: The y coordinate of the node
        nodeInfo - String: Short describing information about the node
